AI Layer (Live Ryu Integration)

This project trains and evaluates a DQN agent that optimizes SDN behavior against a real Ryu controller.

Pipeline contract

- Startup phase (one-time): apply routing foundation and baseline QoS.
- Runtime phase (per RL step): apply optimization-only actions.

Runtime state and actions

- State: 6D normalized vector
  - latency
  - packet_loss
  - throughput
  - main_link_util
  - backup_link_util
  - failover_active
- Actions: 4 discrete controls
  - 0 do_nothing
  - 1 update_queue
  - 2 failover
  - 3 reroute

Core modules

1. ai_layer/network_setup/network_initializer.py
- Runs one-time startup setup for routing + baseline QoS from prod.json.

2. ai_layer/network_interface/ryu_client.py
- HTTP client with retry/error handling.
- Telemetry endpoints:
  - GET /links/utilization
  - GET /latency/{src}/{dst}
- Setup/action endpoints:
  - PUT /v1.0/conf/switches/{switch_id}/ovsdb_addr
  - POST /router/{switch_id}
  - POST /qos/queue/{switch_id}
  - POST /qos/rules/{switch_id}

3. ai_layer/network_interface/telemetry_parser.py
- Converts live telemetry to 6D operational state.

4. ai_layer/network_interface/action_translator.py
- Maps runtime action ID to concrete Ryu API calls.
- Returns ActionResult(success, message, metadata).

5. ai_layer/environments/sdn_env.py
- Live Gymnasium environment with stabilization delay and optional reset endpoint call.

6. ai_layer/utils/reward.py
- Operational QoS reward with decomposed components.

7. train.py / evaluate.py / clint_test.py
- Config-driven train/eval/smoke flows with optional startup setup call.

Quick start

1. Install dependencies
   pip install -r requirements.txt

2. Run one-time startup setup
   python setup_network.py --config prod.json

3. Run smoke test
   python clint_test.py

4. Train
   python train.py --config prod.json --model-path models/dqn_model_live.pth

5. Evaluate
   python evaluate.py --config prod.json --model-path models/dqn_model_live.pth
